<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We focused on VPNs that actually prove they don’t keep logs, not just say so. That means we looked for real third-party audits and clear security practices. We checked if each VPN had recent audits covering their servers, RAM-only networks, and encryption, plus their privacy policies. If their security documentation made sense, that means that it is a secure VPN for crypto. Finding the <b>best no log vpn</b> was a priority in our security scoring.</span></p>
