<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">From a legal standpoint, VPNs are widely used for privacy, remote work, and online security. Governments generally don’t care if you’re using a VPN to protect your internet connection. In most regions, the answer to &#8220;<b>is it legal to use vpn for crypto trading</b>?&#8221; is yes.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exchanges, however, are a different story. Platforms like Binance, Bybit, or regional exchanges must comply with licensing rules. If their terms say “no VPN usage” or restrict access by location, violating those terms can trigger internal enforcement even if you haven’t broken any laws.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">KYC Conflicts</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">KYC (Know Your Customer) is where VPN usage becomes truly sensitive. During verification, exchanges expect your digital footprint to match the information on your documents including your country of residence.</span></p>
